{{! Uniform "claim unavailable" page.

    Rendered when a claim against a historical-person record cannot proceed
    for any reason: the record does not exist, has already been claimed, is
    already linked to a legacy account, the surname on the record does not
    match the requesting account, the requesting account is linked to an
    incompatible legacy record, or any other validation failure. The page
    intentionally does NOT distinguish between these cases: all failure
    reasons map to the same response so the page cannot confirm which
    person IDs exist (anti-enumeration). The operator can resolve the
    specific cause from the application log written at render time.
}}

<div class="hero hero-sm">
  <div>
    <h1>{{page.title}}</h1>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper">
  <section>
    <p>We could not link this historical record to your account. If you believe this is your record, please contact an IFPA administrator and reference the URL of this page.</p>

    <p class="mt-4"><a href="{{content.contactAdminHref}}" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Admin</a></p>

    <p class="mt-6"><a href="{{content.cancelHref}}">Back to the record</a> &middot; <a href="/register/wizard/legacy_claim">Back to the onboarding wizard</a></p>
  </section>
</div>
